This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for domain adaptation using metric learning on manifolds. The paper also presents detailed experiments using standard transfer learning testbeds from computer vision, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the paper mentions using diffusions on the underlying source and target manifolds, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
